# 4-bit Up/Down Counter using Verilog

## 📌 Overview

This project implements a **4-bit Up/Down Counter** in Verilog HDL. The counter can count either **up** or **down** depending on the value of the control input (`up_down`). It also includes an **active-high asynchronous reset** to initialize the counter to `0000`.

This project demonstrates sequential logic, conditional statements inside clocked always blocks, and the use of control signals to change circuit behavior.

---

## ✨ Features

- 4-bit synchronous Up/Down Counter
- Positive edge-triggered operation
- Active-high asynchronous reset
- Counts Up when `up_down = 1`
- Counts Down when `up_down = 0`
- Wrap-around counting
- Synthesizable Verilog HDL

